     * Foreword and Table of Contents
     * Section 1: The Aviation Weather Service Program
     * Section 2: Aviation Routine Weather Report (METAR)
     * Section 3: Pilot and Radar Reports, Satellite Pictures, and
       Radiosonde Additional Data (RADATs)
     * Section 4: Aviation Weather Forecasts
     * Section 5: Surface Analysis Chart
     * Section 6: Weather Depiction Chart
     * Section 7: Radar Summary Chart
     * Section 8: Constant Pressure Analysis Charts
     * Section 9: Composite Moisture Stability Chart
     * Section 10: Winds and Temperatures Aloft Charts
     * Section 11: Significant Weather Prognostic Charts
     * Section 12: Convective Outlook Chart
     * Section 13: Volcanic Ash Advisory Center (VAAC) Products
     * Section 14: Turbulence Locations, Conversion and Density Altitude
       Tables, Contractions and Acronyms, Schedule of Products, National
       Weather Service Station Identifiers, WSR-88D Sites, and Internet
       Addresses

National Convective Weather Forecast (NCWF)

   The National Convective Weather Forecast (NCWF) is a new aviation
   weather product recently approved by the FAAs Aviation Weather
   Technology Transfer Board.  The NCWF is an automatically generated
   depiction of current convection and extrapolated significant current
   convection.  It is a supplement (not a substitute) to convective
   SIGMETs. Used in conjunction with other weather products such as
   convective SIGMETs, the NCWF provides additional information for
   convective weather avoidance and flight planning.  Detailed information
   on the NCWF.

   The NCWF is available from the Aviation Weather Center's Aviation
   Digital Data Service (ADDS), and selecting Convection.

   For further information on NCWF, please contact the FAA Flight
   Operations Branch, AFS-410,  Hooper Harris, at (202) 267-7186 or by
   emailing hooper.harris@faa.gov.
